  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Best practices have shown that performing IUV in a non-production environment is preferable. DOORS (release 9.3 or&#xD;
    higher)&amp;nbsp;should be installed in a non-production ‘sandbox’ environment with appropriate license allocated to this&#xD;
    sandbox.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To prepare DOORS for IUV, you must perform three primary steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Install DOORS in a non-production sandbox.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create two users. One each with database manager and standard user access.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Restore the DOORS IUV Project Archive&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To install DOORS, follow the procedure outlined in the DOORS online help: &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/doorshlp/v9/topic/com.ibm.doors.install.doc/topics/c_planninginstallationorupgrade.html&quot;>http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/doorshlp/v9/topic/com.ibm.doors.install.doc/topics/c_planninginstallationorupgrade.html&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To create new users, follow the procedure outlined in the DOORS online help: &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/doorshlp/v9/topic/com.ibm.doors.administering.doc/topics/c_optionsmanageusersgroups.html&quot;>http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/doorshlp/v9/topic/com.ibm.doors.administering.doc/topics/c_optionsmanageusersgroups.html&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The IUV information is stored in a DOORS Project Archive here: &amp;lt;link&amp;gt;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When performing the restore, give the project a descriptive name that will be easy for others to identify. For Example:&#xD;
    DOORS Full IUV Project &amp;lt;date&amp;gt;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To restore a project archive, follow the procedure outlined in the DOORS online help: &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/doorshlp/v9/topic/com.ibm.doors.administering.doc/topics/t_restoreprojectoramodule.html&quot;>http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/doorshlp/v9/topic/com.ibm.doors.administering.doc/topics/t_restoreprojectoramodule.html&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
